      materials: [],
      materials_text:
        '{"blocks":[{"key":"1dfgr","text":"Personal equipment","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":18}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"a8ri6","text":"Head torch with red function capability","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6qp4b","text":"Thin tip permanent marker for labelling throughout the protocol and for the prevention of contamination between genotypes","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":26,"length":95}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"83fra","text":"White tape for labelling spawning and gamete collection equipment with genotype identification","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":11,"length":83}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"d89no","text":" ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"e6rpo","text":"Tools/perishables ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":18}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5pr4m","text":"Pipettes (3 sizes: 2-20ul, 2-200ul, 200 -1000ul)","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fqq24","text":"Disposable pipette tips for each size ","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3muuo","text":"Eppendorf tube 1.5ml or 2ml This choice depends on which tube is used in the downstream DNA extraction as Symbiodiniaceae cells will be snap-frozen directly into 1.5ml or 2ml tubes ready for extraction","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":28,"length":173}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"js9u","text":"Regular spawning and gamete washing equipment (e.g bowls, cups, tape, marker, 100um or 50um filter) ","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"df7au","text":"Plastic transfer pipettes","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"f3l79","text":"15ml or 10ml falcon tubes (approx. 10 tubes for each colony (genotype) that spawns) Ideally, the number of falcon tubes is kept even at this stage for ease of immediate centrifugation","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":84,"length":99}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"36bcs","text":"Electric pipette (e.g: Eppendorf Easypet 3) These are necessary for pipette mixing to resuspend pellet in the large volume 10ml or 15ml falcon tubes ","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":44,"length":104}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"agb8m","text":"Disposable serological pipette tips for electric pipette (tip size: 10ml or 15ml both sizes will fit into the electric pipette)","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":81,"length":45}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"f85se","text":"Haemocytometer ","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8kf5t","text":"Counting machine/click counter","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"a5o4a","text":"Styrofoam 2ml tube rack for snap-freezing directly in tube on shallow bath (small Esky lid) of liquid nitrogen","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":24,"length":86}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"57k9v","text":"Liquid nitrogen ","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"e3ufg","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"cnl2j","text":"Equipment/instruments ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":22}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"69m7b","text":"Falcon tube rack helpful for moving around at night with samples from tanks to lab and within the lab between centrifugation rounds and washes","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":17,"length":125}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3gu68","text":"Benchtop centrifuge any benchtop centrifuge capable \\u003c/=3,500 x g will work ","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":20,"length":55}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"dv0ll","text":"Microcentrifuge must fit 1.5 or 2ml Eppendorf for the final spin down to a pellet of known cell count prior to snap-freezing","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":16,"length":108}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"q5k9","text":"High-power microscope","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8gm9h","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6p22g","text":"The ideal benchtop centrifuge is the Allegra V-15R with a maximum speed/RCF of 13,500 RPM /20,412 x g. However, if this is not available, a benchtop centrifuge with a lower maximum speed can be used, such as the Allegra X-12R with a maximum speed/RCF of 3,750 RPM / 3,270 x g. In the case of using a centrifuge which does not match the maximum speed of the protocol, simply use the maximum speed possible of the available benchtop centrifuge.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":0,"length":442}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6lrv4","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"b85k5","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"bkjn7","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fmv7c","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"94igf","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}',
